Perfect 👍 I’ll put together a **single script** that:

1. Installs build dependencies
2. Builds and installs the latest **libplist** (>= 2.6.0, required by libtatsu)
3. Builds and installs the latest **libtatsu**
4. Refreshes linker + pkg-config paths

This will work in a **Pixel full Linux environment**. If you’re inside **Termux/proot (no sudo)**, I’ll also give you a local-user version.

---

## 🔹 Script (system-wide install, with sudo)

Save this as `build_libtatsu.sh` and run:

```bash
#!/bin/bash
set -e

# Install dependencies
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y git build-essential autoconf automake libtool pkg-config checkinstall \
                   libssl-dev libcurl4-openssl-dev

# Build and install latest libplist
if [ ! -d libplist ]; then
  git clone https://github.com/libimobiledevice/libplist.git
fi
cd libplist
./autogen.sh
make
sudo make install
cd ..

# Refresh linker
sudo ldconfig

# Build and install latest libtatsu
if [ ! -d libtatsu ]; then
  git clone https://github.com/libimobiledevice/libtatsu.git
fi
cd libtatsu
./autogen.sh
make
sudo make install
cd ..

# Refresh linker again
sudo ldconfig

echo "✅ libplist and libtatsu installed successfully!"
```

Run it:

```bash
chmod +x build_libtatsu.sh
./build_libtatsu.sh
```

---

## 🔹 Script (local install, no sudo – for Termux/proot)

If you don’t have `sudo`, use this version instead:

```bash
#!/bin/bash
set -e

PREFIX=$HOME/.local
mkdir -p $PREFIX

# Install dependencies via apt (where possible)
apt update
apt install -y git build-essential autoconf automake libtool pkg-config

# Build and install latest libplist locally
if [ ! -d libplist ]; then
  git clone https://github.com/libimobiledevice/libplist.git
fi
cd libplist
./autogen.sh --prefix=$PREFIX
make
make install
cd ..

# Build and install latest libtatsu locally
if [ ! -d libtatsu ]; then
  git clone https://github.com/libimobiledevice/libtatsu.git
fi
cd libtatsu
./autogen.sh --prefix=$PREFIX
make
make install
cd ..

# Export paths for pkg-config & linker
echo "export PKG_CONFIG_PATH=$PREFIX/lib/pkgconfig:\$PKG_CONFIG_PATH" >> ~/.bashrc
echo "export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$PREFIX/lib:\$LD_LIBRARY_PATH" >> ~/.bashrc
echo "export PATH=$PREFIX/bin:\$PATH" >> ~/.bashrc

echo "✅ libplist and libtatsu installed locally in $PREFIX"
echo "⚠️ Restart your shell or run: source ~/.bashrc"
```

---

✅ After this, you’ll have both `libplist >= 2.6.0` and `libtatsu` installed on your Pixel Linux environment.
Then you can continue with **palera1n setup**.

